				 Email targets Pak team
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Nov. 24: An email threatening more terror strikes, including on the Pakistani cricket team, was received by a TV channel today.																								Security agencies are on their toes as a similar mail was received by TV channels minutes after the Varanasi court complex blast yesterday.																								Todays mail, sent from the id guru_boys2000yahoo.com, has apparently specified the dates on which the blasts will take place in metros and satellite towns. It has demanded that the Pakistani team should go home.																								The authenticity of the mail is being verified. A home ministry official said appropriate action was being taken on the email.																								BCCI vice-president Rajiv Shukla said: We have decided to beef up the security for the Pakistan team, both at the hotel and the ground. We are also taking special care for the security of the spectators.																								The email warning of yesterdays synchronised court complex blasts in Uttar Pradesh was sent from the id guru_alhindiyahoo.fr. It has been traced to a cyber caf, Rajdhani, in east Delhi.																								The cyber caf owner is being questioned. 
